{
  "text": "We did not observe any long-term systemic toxicity associated with vancomycin or butyrate treatment. We observed gradual but transient weight loss in the group Figure 6 . VSMC migration in presence of sodium butyrate. (A). Subconfluent VSMC were treated with sodium butyrate in 10% serum conditions. There is a qualitative dose-dependent decrease in the number of cells filling in a scratch over 24 h. (B). Migrated VSMC in transwells were counted per high-powered field (HPF) and migrated cells were expressed as mean number AE SEM. Representative of N = 3. *P < 0.05 relative to 10% serum group. treated with vancomycin+butyrate, which we attribute to a period of accommodation necessary for the rats to become accustomed to the odor and taste of butyrate [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ). We addressed this by changing the water frequently. We also did not observe any diarrhea (loose or watery stool pellets) in any of the 151 stool pellets that were collected over all timepoints in all treatment groups.",
  "correct_citation": {
